{"questionId":"5275605","questionHtml":"<p>A ball is projected at an angle to the horizonal on Earth reaching a maximum height <em>H</em> and a maximum range <em>R</em>. The same ball is projected at the same angle and speed on a planet where the acceleration due to gravity is three times that on Earth. Resistance effects are negligible.</p>\n<p>What is the maximum range and the maximum height reached on that planet?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"height:269px;border-color:#000000;width:411px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:66.5833px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width:159.35px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Maximum range</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:165.067px;text-align:center;\">\n<strong>Maximum height</strong><br><strong>reached</strong>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:66.5833px;\">A.</td>\n<td style=\"width:159.35px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:165.067px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>H</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:66.5833px;\">B.</td>\n<td style=\"width:159.35px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:165.067px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>H</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:66.5833px;\">C.</td>\n<td style=\"width:159.35px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:165.067px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>H</mi><mn>9</mn></mfrac></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:66.5833px;\">D.</td>\n<td style=\"width:159.35px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:165.067px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>H</mi><mn>9</mn></mfrac></math></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"5275605","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ1.5","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A ball is projected at an angle to the horizonal on Earth reaching a maximum height H and a maximum range R. The same ball is projected at the same angle and speed on a planet wher","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"5","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","2.1 – Motion","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}